<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> Wizard regens about 250+110 mana per minute = 360 mana/min. He casts ice spear of the soloist for 300 mana for a max hit of 1200. So the wizard can do 1440 per minute damage with that spell.<br>
<br>
A meele has to deal 24 DPS to beat him. In grind groups with speed I currently deal between 50-70 DPS. About 2-3 times as much as the wizard. On raids I deal around 40-50DPS but also heal a significant amount of AoE damage.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Add spells that do <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> huge</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> damage for moderate mana... yet have long cast times and longer recast times.<br>
<br>
A Paladin does 70 DPS you say?  that's 4200 DPM.<br>
<br>
So a spell that takes 120 mana, does 1400 damage has a cast time of 5 seconds recast time of 15 seconds would produce the exact same DPM with a MCPM of 360.<br>
<br>
This would, of course, have to be a very rare spell... but a few spells that aren't <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> quite</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> this good, perhaps with situational modifiers (only useable underground, not against Undead, etc) would produce very favorable effects.<br>
<br>
Don't forget that AoE spells throw DPM right out the window.  If you've got an AoE spell that does 800 damage, then that's potentially 3200 damage (or lots more, if it doesn't have limited targets).  In an AoE group, a Wizard's DPM beats <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> anyones</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ugraalthedorf.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Graal the Dorf</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 198<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/5/02 4:06:36 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=14722.topic&index=24>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Caster Balancing</span><hr size=1> The one thing that makes caster-melee out of whack is how much items increase the power of melee classes, but don't do nearly the same for casters. Each expansion has dramatically increased the power of the melee classes with the introduction of better items. If you compare the best weapons available in kunark to the best weapons available now, you can see that melee damage output has essentially doubled since kunark.<br>
<br>
One of the gripes that casters have is that there is so much good gear flooding the lower levels that most melee classes can outdamage casters considerably. A level 30 paladin with one of the decent DN 2 handers, some DW/barbed ringmail armor, an FBSS, and a fungi is going to be able to solo much better than any caster his level, regardless of the gear the caster has.<br>
<br>
The same thing is true at higher levels. That is why VI is introducing so many FT items, it is their attempt to allow items to enhance casters in a meaningful way. They are also using the ancient spells to try to fix this problem. The only other thing I can think of doing is spell casting haste on items and more/better focus items for pet classes. <p>Graal MacBladefury<BR>
