<br>
Why?<br>
<br>
Because they would *DIE*! <br>
<br>
They would steal aggro from the melee, and fold after one serious hit. They don't have the HP or AC to take the blows.<br>
<br>
The purpose of caster damage is tactical Nuker.<br>
<br>
Delay, disrupt, and finish off the mobs.  Nuke at 80% to knock it down a bit, nuke to get it into 'flee' mode, nuke to fry a runner.<br>
<br>
I cannot tell you how much I love grouping with a wizard or other nuker that knows *when* to nuke.  They are almost as valuable as a healer who knows when to heal.<br>
<br>
Sure, give them spells with a shorter casting time, but *DON'T* let them out damage their meat shields in the long haul. <br>
<br>
Comparing casters, INT WIS or hybrid by the ridiculous term of DPS or DPM is a silly nearsighted game.<br>
<br>
Now, does it suck that Mages and Necros become merely mana banks for high level raids?<br>
<br>
Yes.<br>
<br>
I have only played a Paladin up to lvl 30. So, yes I am completely ignorant of the "High Level Game" and casters abilities at that level.<br>
<br>
*BUT*<br>
<br>
I do know that Verant has spent a lot of time giving each class distinct sets of skills and abilities. And that tactics and strategies for each class change over time.<br>
<br>
They are probably going to provide more variety to the capabilities of high level casters.<br>
<br>
I hope to the gods for the casters' sake that they do *NOT* make a wizard / mage / necro whomever capable of out damaging their meat shields.<br>
<br>
I also hope that casters realize that pulling out the DTS yardstick is like taking a ruler to your crotch.<br>
<br>
The measurement doesn't matter, knowing how and when to use it does. . .  <p><img src=http://members.bellatlantic.net/~vze2vw5m/sigpic.jpg></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uangelsyn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Angelsyn</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://members.aol.com/tdlutenatenjou/icon_keyne.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 105<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/6/02 7:01:08 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=14722.topic&index=31>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://members.aol.com/tdlutenatenjou/icon_keyne.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Casters DTS parity w/ Meatshields?  NO WAY</span><hr size=1> Faster casting spells are not the answer...<br>
